GENERAL INFORMATION
Reservations
Reservations may be made through a travel agent, Pioneer Airlines, or
any domestic or international airline. Pioneer will be happy to make
reservations for your entire trip including any connecting flights.
Check-In Time Before Flight Departure
If you need to be ticketed, please be at Pioneer's airport ticket counter
forty-five minutes prior to flight time. If you have your tickets, please
check-in thirty minutes before.
Passengers checking in less than ten minutes prior to departure, even if
ticketed, are subject to having reservations cancelled.
Responsibility for Departure/Arrival Times and Connections
Pioneer makes every effort to operate on-time. Because weather and
other conditions may affect operations, Pioneer Airlines will not be res-
ponsible for damages resulting from failure to depart or arrive at the
times stated in this timetable, nor for failure to make connections with
other carriers or this company, nor for cancellations when such action is
deemed advisable. Schedules and fares are subject to change without
notice. All times shown are local times.
Baggage
Free allowance for two pieces (forty pound maximum) plus one carry-on
which will fit under the seat. If carry-on cannot be placed beneath the
seat, it will be collected and placed in a cargo compartment. Excess
baggage will be boarded for destination on a space available basis and at
an additional charge.
Pioneer will check baggage to connecting flights to your final destination
if you desire.
Restricted articles and corrosive liquids, flammable substances, com-
pressed
gas or any hazardous material may not be carried in
baggage.
Baggage Liability
Baggage must be identifiable with your name and address clearly marked
on the outside of each piece. Liability for loss or damage to checked
baggage is limited to $500.00 unless a higher value is declared and
applicable charges are paid before departure. Excess valuation cannot be
declared for jewelry, negotiable instruments, currency or antiques, nor will
Pioneer accept any liability for loss or damage of such checked items.
Form of Payment
Pioneer Airlines accepts American Express, Bank Americard/Visa, Mas-
terCard, UATP, Diners Club, Carte Blanche credit cards, personal and
corporate checks with proper ID, and cash.
Ticket Refund
Tickets purchased from other airlines or travel agents must be refunded
by issuing party. Tickets purchased from Pioneer may be mailed to the
corporate office for a refund.
Freight, Small Package and Express Services are Available
Contact the local Pioneer representative or reservations for rates and
information.
Special Fares
Pioneer offers many money saving discounts. For details contact your
travel agent or Pioneer Airlines.
Equipment
Pioneer operates twin turboprop pressurized Metro III aircraft with two
FAA Commercial licensed pilots.
PIONEER AIRLINES
Corporate Offices
Hangar 5
Stapleton International Airport
Denver, Colorado 80207
2015126.062
